column5: Hi All,  A favourite shore fishing spot is really producing this fall. Nothing fancy, jigs and large minnows cast into 18' of water and brought back with a jerk..jerk...twitch twitch...pause (repeat). This outing the fish were doing a late shift and took 20 minutes before biting, but for 1 hour it was again a bite a cast and i was home in time to cook it up.   <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/JZTPqGw_Bh8" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
You had to wait a whole 20 minutes....BRUTAL!  Seems like this is quite a gem of a spot....keep the reports coming
Ah .. you are so lucky ...  I paid to fly up there and catch those ...
GLOVES????? just a brutal reminder of things to come Those are some clean healthy looking Eyes Simon! Great report.  Paul
Way to go Simon!!!  Another beauty report!
I was up in Geraldton today but I didn't bring my rod... Probably a few lakes likes that up there I could have hit. Great stuff Simon... Tasty din din
